  <description><![CDATA[<p>With a superb location in the centre of <a data-udi="umb://document/57bc5f34b7074843b7f19f3fc6cb7ac4" href="/{localLink:umb://document/57bc5f34b7074843b7f19f3fc6cb7ac4}" title="Rome">Rome</a>, positioned on a quiet street off Via Veneto, the Ludovisi Palace Hotel offers a modern retreat in a building dating back to the early 1900’s.  The Spanish Steps, the Villa Borghese and the stylish shops of the Via Condotti are all within easy walking distance.</p>
<p>After a day of exploring the Eternal City relax in the Ludovisi Bar and enjoy a drink and delicious appetizers before dinning out.  The hotels concierge is open 24 hours and available to help you book Theatre or Opera shows, is you so wish. </p>
<p>The hotels guest rooms are of an English-style décor with wooden furniture to offer our guests a peaceful stay.  The large windows fill the room with light, offering a bright airy room to unwind from the bustle of the city.     </p>
<p>Transfer time: approx. 1 hour by private car from Rome Fiumicino Airport or approx. 40 mins from Rome Ciampino Airport.</p>]]></description>
